{"type":"message","id":"cebb78ff","parentId":"c2c46dfe","timestamp":"2026-03-04T02:51:05.216Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Okay, let's think differently. The user tried all the methods and login.tailscale.com is accessible, but sign in still doesn't work. Let's check if there's a way to capture the URL that Tailscale is trying to open, maybe using Process Monitor or checking the Tailscale logs more carefully. Wait, let's try to use the --qr flag with tailscale up to get a QR code, which might bypass the browser issue. Or maybe try to get the login URL from the tailscale command output.\n\nWait, let's try running tailscale up --qr in a PowerShell window and see if it outputs a QR code or a login URL. Also, let's check the Windows Event Viewer for Tailscale events.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"好的，让我们尝试一个更直接的方法：通过 Tailscale 命令行获取登录二维码或 URL，绕过 GUI 的 sign in 按钮问题。"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_6nz67omfx60yqrbq1u4j2x91","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"& \"C:\\Program Files\\Tailscale\\tailscale.exe\" up --qr --qr-format=ascii","workdir":"D:\\openclaw\\.openclaw\\workspace"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"ark","model":"doubao-seed-2.0-code","usage":{"input":42123,"output":412,"cacheRead":6200,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":48735,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772592643899}}
